1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,880
So that is your voice on the clip,
Mr. Mahasamut?

2
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:57,120
I can assure you,
that is absolutely not my voice.

3
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,760
I have a way to prove it.

4
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,440
- How?
- What way?

5
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,360
You're very kind.

6
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:06,320
I'm happy to help
if there's anything I can do.

7
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,440
It's great to have
capable people working with us.

8
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,640
- Oh!
- Mr. Wayu.

9
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:21,440
Do you have any way
to help Fahsai become stronger?

10
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:26,080
Hold steady.

11
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,800
I told you that when I get better

12
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:35,960
and stronger,
I'll prove the truth about you.

13
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:38,480
Do you even know
where Ms. Fahsai is going right now?

14
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,120
<i>Before I called you,</i>

15
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:49,120
<i>Ms. Fahsai contacted Commander Singha</i>
<i>and left right away.</i>

16
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:55,560
She's about to reach
the investigation unit right now.

17
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,200
Huh…

18
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:04,640
I thought she was as innocent as her name.

19
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:10,000
We've been watching her this whole time,
and nothing suspicious.

20
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:14,040
And now suddenly,
she's meeting that sly commander?

21
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:17,399
<i>We can't underestimate anyone.</i>

22
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,279
<i>The tracker is still active.</i>

23
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:25,160
We'll find out soon enough
why she went to see Singha.

24
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,520
Yes.

25
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,720
Yong, I'm just running some errands.

26
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:37,760
I'll head back once I'm done.

27
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,920
- Hey!
- Grab him!

28
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,360
The signal's gone.

29
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,400
Sam, what happened?

30
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,320
Hey.

31
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,760
Damn it, do something, Sam.

32
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,360
One moment.

33
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,560
It's not working.

34
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,720
Take him inside.

35
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,840
Go.

36
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,280
Are you okay?

37
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:01,280
Yes.

38
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:13,040
The Jaiaree family case
was closed six years ago.

39
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:15,680
What do you want to know about this case?

40
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:19,560
Yes. Do you remember

41
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:22,840
that I was also abducted
by Somkid that night?

42
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,720
The one who saved me

43
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:30,240
was a medical student named Peeraka.

44
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,600
My father never told you?

45
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:42,640
I asked him to confirm it with the police.

46
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:46,840
Your father doesn't interfere
with investigations.

47
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:51,880
And all the evidence
clearly pointed to the killer.

48
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,840
But the motive that he snapped

49
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:58,080
from academic pressure
was just speculation.

50
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:03,400
And the fire at his house
destroyed all the evidence.

51
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,320
Well?

52
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:12,640
I understand you're emotionally attached.

53
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:17,720
You want to repay someone
you believe saved you.

54
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,920
It's not just emotion.

55
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:23,680
Someone who risks his life
to save a stranger,

56
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,560
could he really kill his own family?

57
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:29,960
You went through trauma that night.

58
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:34,200
What you remember may not be the truth.

59
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:38,200
And the one who saved you
might not have been Peeraka.

60
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,600
I was with him for hours.

61
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,240
I'm certain.

62
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:49,120
But afterward, you underwent
years of therapy, didn't you?

63
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:56,680
I'm willing to reopen the case

64
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:58,280
if he's innocent.

65
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,080
But we need solid evidence.

66
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,400
Come in.

67
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,880
SINGHA SIRITHANA

68
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,360
Excuse me, Commander.

69
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:20,720
Ms. Fahsai, your phone
that shut down when you dropped it,

70
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,320
I had it repaired.

71
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,920
- Thank you.
- Ms. Fahsai.

72
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,520
There's something important
you should know.

73
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:33,440
This is Captain Anawin Pipatpong,

74
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,400
- my subordinate.
- Hello, sir.

75
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:38,400
He discovered that Ms. Fahsai's phone

76
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,880
had been tapped.

77
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,440
Well.

78
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,880
Thank you.

79
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:51,400
By the way, when was it installed?

80
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:55,400
It was installed about three weeks ago.

81
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:03,240
We need to find those people.

82
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,680
Yes, sir.

83
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:07,280
Oh?

84
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:12,520
This is Commander Singha
and Captain Anawin.

85
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,560
This is Wayu, son of Mr. Chaichana.

86
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:19,080
He's been helping Fahsai.

87
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,440
Good afternoon, Commander…

88
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,240
Captain.

89
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:35,360
How could you let this happen?

90
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:40,159
My sister's data has been leaked.
Do you even realize that?

91
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:45,920
Do you know how those evil people
could use that data?

92
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:48,800
This is your responsibility.

93
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:51,880
Didn't you check anything?

94
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:55,040
<i>You call this "evil"?</i>

95
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:00,240
<i>What about what you've done?</i>

96
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,920
It's my fault. I apologize.

97
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,760
Your apology

98
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:13,240
means nothing anymore.

99
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,640
You're dismissed.

100
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:23,280
Hey, hey, wait.

101
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:28,520
Wayu just helped Fahsai improve.

102
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,120
- I think--
- But he failed

103
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,720
when he shouldn't have.

104
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:38,480
It's fine, sir.

105
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:45,720
I'll do as you wish.

106
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:57,520
Yes, Yong? What?

107
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,160
Yes.

108
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:04,480
I have something urgent at the foundation.

109
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:08,360
I'll take my leave now.
We'll discuss Wayu later.

110
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,520
Drive me there.

111
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:16,840
Let's go.

112
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:20,120
Excuse me. I'm in a hurry.

113
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:35,920
Why didn't you tell me

114
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:40,120
that Mr. Chaichana's heir,
who used to cling to you,

115
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,640
looks like Peeraka?

116
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,960
You've met Mr. Wayu?

117
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:46,600
Did something happen?

118
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:50,280
I'll tell you later. But first, answer me.

119
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:56,680
At first, I was shocked too.
He does look a lot like Raka.

120
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,720
But if I'd told you,

121
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:03,320
you would've just told me I was still
obsessing over someone who's already dead.

122
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,800
Every time I see that man,

123
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:09,400
I have to remind myself that Raka is dead.

124
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:12,920
He just gives off
a similar feeling, that's all.

125
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:17,920
And besides,
you told me not to talk about Raka.

126
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,680
So why are you asking about this now?

127
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:24,720
Well, the fact that you never said
anything made me think maybe…

128
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:28,360
maybe you'd fallen for him.

129
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,040
But it's good that you know now.

130
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,600
Your water.

131
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,560
- Your water, <i>oppa</i>.
- Thank you.

132
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:51,320
Ms. Fahsai, it may be a little late,

133
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:55,200
but when the foundation opened,
I never had the chance to visit.

134
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,320
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

135
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,640
Actually, you didn't have to.

136
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,160
Actually, the reason I came today

137
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,520
is because I'd like to ask a favor.

138
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:14,120
But before that, I want you to know

139
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,240
that I really admire you, Ms. Fahsai.

140
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,280
You helped catch that man
who abused his girlfriend.

141
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:24,560
That was very brave.

142
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:30,440
So I brought these flowers
to encourage you.

143
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:35,360
Actually, I can't take all the credit.

144
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,760
Mr. Wayu put himself at greater risk.

145
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:47,400
Yes. Then I really do

146
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,240
owe both of you my thanks.

147
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:53,600
Actually, our party has also had domestic
violence victims come to us for help.

148
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:57,080
But we haven't been able
to do much for them.

149
00:12:57,160 --> 00:13:00,880
We're a new party,
and we don't have many people.

150
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,080
Ms. Fahsai,

151
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:10,480
would it be possible for us to refer
those cases to the Fahsai Foundation?

152
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,280
My gosh…

153
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:17,760
Uh…

154
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:23,200
Well, I know our parties are rivals.

155
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,640
But I don't see that as a barrier

156
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:29,160
to working together to help society.

157
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:39,880
But if you're not comfortable with it,
I understand.

158
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:47,200
Of course. We'd be happy to help.

159
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,000
Thank you very much.

160
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,360
Thank you.

161
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,160
The press is here.

162
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:11,880
Wouldn't this be considered
helping the opposing party score points

163
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:14,200
since you're
on different sides politically?

164
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:18,840
Oh. I don't want people
to see politics as nothing but division.

165
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,200
Just because we belong
to different parties

166
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:24,320
doesn't mean
we have to compete in everything.

167
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,760
What the Fahsai Foundation is doing

168
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,520
is truly helping society.

169
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,120
I fully support it.

170
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,560
Wow.

171
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,760
That's a quote of the year right there.

172
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:39,000
Ms. Fahsai, could we get a photo
of the two of you together?

173
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:45,760
A little closer, please.

174
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:50,680
Mr. Guard, could you step aside a bit?

175
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,360
Just a little more.

176
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:57,360
Wait.

177
00:14:57,440 --> 00:15:00,280
Wait.

178
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,960
Thank you.

179
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:07,000
Wow, so beautiful.

180
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,760
Beautiful.

181
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:14,320
This camera, please.

182
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,840
Nice.

183
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:31,040
Fahsai secretly asked Commander Singha
about the Jaiaree family case?

184
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,680
She didn't tell us.

185
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:39,240
She went to see Singha herself.

186
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:47,040
Then that means she must have
started suspecting something.

187
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:52,280
Calm down.

188
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:57,600
According to the commander, Fahsai
doubts the cause of Peeraka's death,

189
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,800
and she doesn't believe he was the killer.

190
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:03,480
But she has no proof.

191
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:07,200
If she keeps hitting dead ends,

192
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,280
eventually she'll let it go on her own.

193
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,240
Usually, you're more decisive than this.

194
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:20,800
But the second it's about your sister,
you lose control.

195
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,240
Calm down. Don't act suspicious.

196
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,720
No matter what,

197
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:33,440
I believe Fahsai
will ultimately take our side.

198
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:42,280
Sir, a news outlet is livestreaming this.

199
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:52,000
<i>It's really wonderful</i>
<i>to see this social collaboration</i>

200
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,040
<i>between Mr. Tarn's Namjai Thai Party</i>

201
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:57,160
<i>and the Fahsai Foundation,</i>
<i>which is tied to the Numchat Thai Party.</i>

202
00:16:57,240 --> 00:17:00,280
<i>This feels like</i>
<i>a whole new dimension of Thai politics.</i>

203
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:04,400
<i>We want to work together</i>
<i>in order to give back to the people</i>

204
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,480
<i>who voted for us to do this job.</i>

205
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:10,680
<i>Just because we're in different parties</i>
<i>doesn't mean we can't work together.</i>

206
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:12,720
HOT NEWS

207
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:15,240
What the hell is this supposed to mean?

208
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:18,480
Tarn's more dangerous than I thought.

209
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:24,240
He's using us to polish his own image.

210
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:27,560
And if he asks for cooperation like that,
how could Fahsai refuse?

211
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:31,080
I will not let him
get involved with Fahsai.

212
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:44,640
Do you think they're onto us,
that we were the ones wiretapping them?

213
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:48,160
No. But we can't keep
doing things the same way anymore.

214
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:52,480
Too bad we didn't find out
why Fahsai went to see Singha.

215
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:55,440
I'll find out myself later.

216
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:56,720
Later?

217
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,520
Didn't you already agree to quit?

218
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,600
That was necessary at the time.

219
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:05,680
I had to prove my sincerity to them.

220
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:10,640
Then let's see if they actually buy it.

221
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,480
Mahasamut just texted me.

222
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:21,400
What does he say?

223
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:26,960
An invitation to a party.
I can bring two friends.

224
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:32,320
A fancy politician's party.
Bring two friends?

225
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,160
I'm in.

226
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,720
Don't you have a date tonight?

227
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,120
I was about to look cool…

228
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,840
See? She just left her house.

229
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:53,600
Come on, at your level?
Just reschedule the date. Easy.

230
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:58,360
No. You're not canceling. That woman
is a source in a case we're working on.

231
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,920
Go do your job.

232
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:14,280
Guess I'll have to change
my gender if you want me in.

233
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,440
We don't have a choice then.

234
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:31,560
Well, there's a new episode of the anime
I'm watching tonight,

235
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,720
so I was planning to stay in--

236
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,480
Hey, hey.

237
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:39,320
Don't chicken out.
You're the only one left. Look.

238
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,520
Two people, done.

239
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:51,040
Where's the party?

240
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:10,800
Go all out. Don't hold back.

241
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,560
Tonight's on me.

242
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:22,600
Didn't expect you
to bring your bodyguards along.

243
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,640
Oh.

244
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:29,120
If we work together, we party together.

245
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:31,680
Good.

246
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,080
I remember him.

247
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:41,480
Is he the one who helped me
with that audio clip?

248
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,440
Then this is perfect.

249
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:51,440
I can treat him properly tonight.

250
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:57,320
Fon, take good care of him.

251
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,640
Of course, boss.

252
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:02,120
Drink up.

253
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:10,680
About earlier today,
I've thought about it.

254
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:14,360
You've helped me with quite a few things.

255
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:17,200
I shouldn't have lost my temper like that.

256
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:23,280
But it involved my sister.

257
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:27,120
You have siblings too, right?

258
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,800
You understand me, don't you?

259
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,400
Yes.

260
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:36,160
Good.

261
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:42,720
Then I'd like you
to continue looking after Fahsai.

262
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:47,680
And keep an eye on the opposition.

263
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,840
You know who I'm talking about, right?

264
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,280
He likes to use work as an excuse.

265
00:21:57,880 --> 00:22:00,080
Keep him strictly within that boundary.

266
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:04,160
Don't let him
cross the line with my sister.

267
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,560
I trust you

268
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:16,960
not to make the same mistake twice.

269
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:37,400
Come on!

270
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:41,680
Let's go!

271
00:22:52,560 --> 00:22:55,920
Oh, come on.

272
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,760
Come on.

273
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:03,520
Let's go!

274
00:23:15,440 --> 00:23:16,680
Come on!

275
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:39,960
Where are you headed, sir?

276
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:49,040
To the restroom.

277
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:53,880
That way?

278
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:56,800
Alright.

279
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,680
Sorry, sir. This is a private zone.

280
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:29,440
I just needed somewhere quiet
to take a call. It's way too loud.

281
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:56,560
Bottoms up! Bottoms up! Bottoms up!

282
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,400
You've wandered pretty far, haven't you?

283
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,480
See anything interesting around here?

284
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:17,560
Hm?

285
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,920
I was on the phone and got carried away.

286
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:27,840
I ended up here without realizing it.

287
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:32,080
Must've been quite a long conversation

288
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,400
to walk this far.

289
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:40,200
I've wasted enough time having fun.
I should head back.

290
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,560
I asked you.

291
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:49,840
What exactly are you doing
in my private zone?

292
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,840
I didn't know this was your private zone.

293
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,640
Really?

294
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:06,880
You seem like the kind of man

295
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:09,320
who gets more curious
the more he's warned off.

296
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:15,640
Do you know

297
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:20,000
why I chose this place as my private zone?

298
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,160
Because it's soundproof.

299
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:40,560
Even the sound of this…

300
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:43,360
barely gets heard.

301
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:55,440
I'm asking you.

302
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:00,280
What are you doing here?

303
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:08,640
You know,

304
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:13,120
people who don't tell me the truth

305
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:16,200
are at great risk of never speaking again.

306
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:26,800
I've got it.

307
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:29,880
Oops, boss.

308
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:37,600
Sorry I didn't tell you.

309
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:41,040
I just…

310
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:43,880
couldn't hold back.

311
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:51,520
So I asked her to come
somewhere quiet so we could talk.

312
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:59,600
So it was just that?

313
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,120
Next time, you can just tell me.

314
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:04,360
There are many places better than this.

315
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:09,280
I'll excuse myself, then. Let's go.

316
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,840
Thanks for sending someone to help.

317
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:39,040
I knew you didn't bring me here
just to have fun.

318
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:43,640
What a shame.
We finally found a way in there

319
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:45,920
and still didn't get any leads at all.

320
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,360
Come on.

321
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:52,120
At least now we know
there's nothing left anymore.

322
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,560
They cleaned up everything.

323
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:58,320
Then let's just count that
as crossing one more place off the list.

324
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:00,960
Which means we can stop
focusing on Heaven Club.

325
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:06,480
Yes.

326
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:09,720
Please provide the code, sir.

327
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:13,920
Ribeye steak with spicy sauce, correct?

328
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:31,800
Your order has arrived.
Ribeye steak with spicy sauce.

329
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:43,360
Your order has arrived.
Ribeye steak with spicy sauce.

330
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:44,800
Please come in.

331
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:57,400
Today's orders have all been
delivered, sir. Thirteen orders.

332
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:59,800
Any complaints about our hotels yet?

333
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,280
None at all, sir.

334
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:05,160
Ever since we started delivering the food
to each hotel in our network

335
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:08,200
and to our close partners,

336
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:10,640
clients haven't had
any concerns about privacy.

337
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:14,120
Back when we served everything
only through Heaven Club,

338
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,920
we got a lot more complaints.

339
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:21,480
That's because everyone had to come here.

340
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:25,120
But once that journalist
snuck in and found out,

341
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:27,960
we had to shut down that VIP room.

342
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:31,280
And it turns out

343
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:34,480
we've spread out everywhere instead.

344
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:37,920
Like a Wi-Fi signal.

345
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:44,120
Our service now has wider
and better coverage than ever.

346
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:50,200
What should I call it?

347
00:31:51,120 --> 00:31:53,400
Honestly, I should thank that woman

348
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:56,200
for turning a crisis into an opportunity.

349
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:13,680
Morning, Dad.

350
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:18,240
Did my people check thoroughly

351
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:21,200
that there are no more
eavesdropping devices around you?

352
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,560
They said there weren't any.

353
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:30,360
I still can't believe someone put one
in my bag without me knowing.

354
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:35,000
If you're dating a politician,
you need to be more careful than this.

355
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:39,840
It was only because
Fahsai's phone got tapped

356
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:42,480
that we suspected yours
might have been too.

357
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:52,800
There was one time I argued with Mr. Samut

358
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:56,040
and we ended up talking about
how I used to date Peeraka.

359
00:32:58,280 --> 00:33:02,120
But that was all.
We didn't say anything else.

360
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:05,240
You need to come up
with a good explanation.

361
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,760
Just in case this gets out

362
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:10,920
and someone ties it back to that case.

363
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:20,040
So that's why you called me here?

364
00:33:20,120 --> 00:33:21,080
No.

365
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:24,320
I have something for you to do.

366
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,560
That man Wayu…

367
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:32,000
I want to test something about him.

368
00:33:36,040 --> 00:33:38,120
Give me your paw. Give me your paw.

369
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,760
The other one. The other one.

370
00:33:40,840 --> 00:33:43,360
Okay, wait.

371
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:46,600
I'll make it for you, okay?
Wait a sec, Kaitod.

372
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:50,040
I'll feed you. Here.

373
00:33:50,720 --> 00:33:51,600
Here.

374
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:57,640
Were you that hungry?

375
00:33:58,560 --> 00:33:59,880
Here, one more bite.

376
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:10,239
Hello?

377
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,000
Here, Captain.

378
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:22,520
- It really is blood.
- It has to be Black Dog.

379
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:26,480
I saw him run this way, but when I
chased after him, I couldn't find anyone.

380
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:28,159
Just these bloodstains.

381
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:32,560
I looked everywhere
and couldn't find him, so I called you.

382
00:34:32,639 --> 00:34:35,960
You did the right thing.
It would've been dangerous.

383
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:39,400
I'll call for backup
and have them search the whole area.

384
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:41,280
You go wait back at the hospital first.

385
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:44,320
But if we wait for backup,
he might disappear by then.

386
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:47,000
I think we should follow the blood now.

387
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:49,719
Hey.

388
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:06,600
This alley's a dead end.
I'm sure he's behind there.

389
00:35:22,640 --> 00:35:25,320
Black Dog! How are you?

390
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:30,240
Huh? Black Dog?

391
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:35,400
That's the Black Dog you were looking for?

392
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:38,840
Yes. He was hit by a car.

393
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:42,440
I was treating him,
but something scared him, and he ran off.

394
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:46,040
Look, he's bleeding everywhere.

395
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:49,080
Captain,

396
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:54,040
could you help me carry him?
I can't lift him.

397
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:01,120
He's only 40 kilos.

398
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:18,000
Excuse me. Coffee delivery.

399
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,320
Huh?

400
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:26,040
Are you sure this isn't a mistake?
Nobody here ordered anything.

401
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:27,520
No, sir.

402
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:30,120
Eight Americanos, ten hot espressos,

403
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:33,320
and 30 croissants.
Delivery for Captain Anawin.

404
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,640
Don't tell me it's COD.
I don't have any money.

405
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:39,000
What's going on?

406
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:42,160
Captain, why'd you order so much coffee?

407
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:45,000
- I didn't order anything.
- Oh?

408
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:50,800
I did.

409
00:36:53,520 --> 00:36:57,400
I wanted to thank you for helping me
find Black Dog the other day.

410
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:59,360
Huh? Black Doc?!

411
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:02,080
Not that Black Doc, Sergeant.

412
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:06,440
This one's an actual black dog
from the hospital that got loose.

413
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:07,400
A real black dog.

414
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:09,640
Oh.

415
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:12,080
If it weren't for you,
he'd probably be dead by now.

416
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,880
I didn't know how to thank you,

417
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:17,320
so I thought I'd treat
the whole department instead.

418
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:19,200
Thank you very much.
Right this way, please.

419
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:20,640
This way, please.

420
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:21,760
Wow.

421
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,200
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

422
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:25,360
Normally we only get cheap
iced coffee around here.

423
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:27,720
It's still hot.

424
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:32,120
Sir.

425
00:37:32,200 --> 00:37:33,640
Captain, you're not drinking coffee?

426
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:40,200
Oh no! I'm so sorry!

427
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,600
- I'm really sorry, Captain.
- It's okay.

428
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:53,560
That's so sweet.

429
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:59,680
I'll just go clean up
in the restroom first.

430
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:02,560
Sergeant, take her into my office.

431
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:03,760
Yes, sir.

432
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:10,320
- This way, please.
- Thank you.

433
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:16,760
This way, please.

434
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:20,400
- Captain will be here in just a moment.
- Thank you.

435
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:48,000
MONTHLY CASE

436
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:14,320
Hello, Ms. Maysa. What can I do for you?

437
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:19,000
Well, well, Mr. Wayu. Why so distant?

438
00:39:19,520 --> 00:39:23,280
Last time, I owed you dinner.

439
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:25,800
So today I'd like to make it up to you.

440
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:27,920
Don't you have work today?

441
00:39:29,040 --> 00:39:32,400
I've got a little bit
of shooting left, but…

442
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:34,720
I don't really want to go home yet.

443
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:38,040
I'd rather spend some time with you first.

444
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:42,640
I want you to get
a strand of his hair or his nails.

445
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:45,120
I'm going to test his DNA.

446
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,640
Didn't you say you didn't
want me involved with him?

447
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:53,400
You told me not to make Mr. Samut unhappy.

448
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:56,880
This is an important case.

449
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,560
Just do it once.

450
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:02,520
Mr. Mahasamut doesn't have to know.

451
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:07,320
- What if I say no?
- You don't have the right to refuse.

452
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:11,720
This is about the survival of us all.

453
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:17,480
So you agree, right?

454
00:40:26,120 --> 00:40:29,520
Hey. Why didn't you answer
the reporters properly?

455
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:32,880
You know one wrong answer
and you'll get dragged online.

456
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:34,560
Do you want to get canceled?

457
00:40:40,640 --> 00:40:43,120
Here. Your next script.

458
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:54,640
Yiwa, why does the male lead

459
00:40:54,720 --> 00:40:57,040
suddenly stop caring
about the female lead?

460
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:05,720
Thank you, but I'm busy today.

461
00:41:07,360 --> 00:41:09,400
Are you upset with me about last time?

462
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:13,360
I really couldn't reschedule that day.

463
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:15,760
Just hearing that you care about me
like this…

464
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,080
That's enough for me.

465
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:22,480
Enough that I don't even feel like
having dinner anymore.

466
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:25,120
I have to go.

467
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:29,920
What kind of writing is this?
The character keeps changing.

468
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,600
He chases her, and then he stops.
Who would even watch this?

469
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:36,160
I would.

470
00:41:36,240 --> 00:41:39,480
A guy constantly chasing a girl
is annoying.

471
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:41,640
Who'd chase another person all day long?

472
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:45,640
If he had self-respect, he wouldn't
be chasing someone all the time.

473
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:46,840
Mm.

474
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:49,800
Go home by yourself today.

475
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:52,240
- I want to be alone.
- Oh?

476
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:56,800
I can go by myself,
but I'm claiming the taxi fare.

477
00:42:05,080 --> 00:42:06,280
Mr. Wayu?

478
00:42:10,440 --> 00:42:13,280
So, are you still free today?

479
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:38,400
Why didn't we go somewhere fancy?
Someplace with a nice atmosphere?

480
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:40,080
Why come to my house instead?

481
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:46,080
Because this is the most luxurious place
with the best atmosphere.

482
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:53,200
I'm an actress.
Wherever I go, I'm under scrutiny.

483
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,840
But here,

484
00:42:54,920 --> 00:42:58,800
we can be ourselves the most.
Isn't that better?

485
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:03,560
That's true.

486
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:09,360
There's no place
where you can be more open than here.

487
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:14,880
I've filmed here several times.

488
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:19,160
I can tell the owner has great taste.

489
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:23,160
It's just a shame

490
00:43:23,240 --> 00:43:25,560
the crew wasn't allowed upstairs.

491
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:28,120
It must be beautiful, right?

492
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:31,560
Would you like to see it?

493
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:36,560
And if I said yes,

494
00:43:37,160 --> 00:43:39,640
would you really let me?

495
00:43:42,080 --> 00:43:44,800
Well, if home is a place

496
00:43:44,880 --> 00:43:47,600
where we can truly be ourselves,

497
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:53,720
then I'd like to show you
more of who I am as well.

498
00:44:01,760 --> 00:44:02,720
Please.

499
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:06,880
Alright.

500
00:44:32,520 --> 00:44:35,000
Simple, serious,

501
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:39,480
but with a playful touch.
It suits you perfectly.

502
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:43,480
You're very good

503
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:46,320
at reading people through their homes.

504
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:51,640
Really? I'm just saying what I see.

505
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:56,640
That way is my bedroom.

506
00:44:58,240 --> 00:44:59,080
Well…

507
00:45:00,200 --> 00:45:01,920
That's too much.

508
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:05,000
Just being up here is already an honor.

509
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:10,040
I'm still curious
what else you can read about me.

510
00:45:13,080 --> 00:45:14,000
Please.

511
00:45:28,760 --> 00:45:30,240
How is it?

512
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:35,240
Just as beautiful as I imagined.

513
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:40,880
And what does this room say about me?

514
00:45:43,040 --> 00:45:45,240
I'm not a Feng Shui expert.

515
00:45:53,280 --> 00:45:54,480
I'm sorry.

516
00:45:55,880 --> 00:45:58,640
I've been showing you around
and forgot to offer you a drink.

517
00:45:59,760 --> 00:46:03,120
- I'm a terrible host.
- It's okay.

518
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:05,360
I might've been talking too much.

519
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:07,320
What would you like to drink?

520
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:13,760
In that case, can I have brandy?

521
00:46:16,200 --> 00:46:17,680
Just a moment.

522
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:50,760
Are you looking for something?

523
00:47:00,880 --> 00:47:03,880
Not only do you have
great taste in home decor,

524
00:47:04,480 --> 00:47:07,080
your choice of perfume
is better than most men's too.

525
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:10,520
It's just a regular perfume.

526
00:47:15,440 --> 00:47:16,680
They say

527
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:20,880
perfume smells different

528
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:23,240
depending on who wears it.

529
00:47:24,480 --> 00:47:26,920
I really understand that today.

530
00:47:37,440 --> 00:47:38,480
Why don't you try it?

531
00:47:39,600 --> 00:47:41,640
On me,

532
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:45,640
it doesn't smell
as good as it does on you.

533
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:15,680
Dinner is ready.

534
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:19,800
Shall we head to the dining room?

535
00:48:22,000 --> 00:48:22,840
Yes.

536
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:26,800
But may I use the bathroom first?

537
00:48:29,480 --> 00:48:30,920
- Alright.
- It's over there.

538
00:48:32,920 --> 00:48:34,040
Thank you.

539
00:49:06,800 --> 00:49:09,880
Do you need any help, Ms. Maysa?

540
00:49:10,880 --> 00:49:11,840
Uh…

541
00:49:12,560 --> 00:49:14,640
Let me just touch up my makeup for a bit.

542
00:50:01,960 --> 00:50:03,880
Let's go. I'm hungry.

543
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:21,200
Thank you.

544
00:50:23,160 --> 00:50:25,040
Just this once, Dad.

545
00:50:25,720 --> 00:50:28,200
Don't make me do
anything this risky again.

546
00:50:29,320 --> 00:50:33,000
If we close this case,
I'll leave you alone.

547
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:50,360
INPATIENT DEPARTMENT
OUTPATIENT DEPARTMENT

548
00:50:50,440 --> 00:50:52,680
Coming down here with you

549
00:50:52,760 --> 00:50:54,280
really made me realize

550
00:50:54,360 --> 00:50:57,360
there are still so many cases
of women and children being abused.

551
00:50:57,880 --> 00:50:59,360
I'm really glad you came.

552
00:50:59,440 --> 00:51:01,760
Even with the foundation we have now,

553
00:51:01,840 --> 00:51:04,000
we still can't handle all the cases.

554
00:51:04,960 --> 00:51:07,360
I'll take your feedback
and improve our party's policies,

555
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:10,360
especially on justice for victims

556
00:51:10,440 --> 00:51:12,760
and long-term care and rehabilitation.

557
00:51:14,320 --> 00:51:17,800
That's wonderful to hear,
for the sake of the people.

558
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:21,640
Well,

559
00:51:21,720 --> 00:51:23,320
it's already noon.

560
00:51:23,400 --> 00:51:26,720
May I treat you to lunch as a thank you?

561
00:51:37,920 --> 00:51:41,040
Lunch while discussing support plans

562
00:51:41,120 --> 00:51:42,680
sounds like a great idea.

563
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:50,320
Please.

564
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:02,440
Let me drive you back to the foundation.

565
00:52:03,400 --> 00:52:05,840
That won't be necessary.
It's my responsibility.

566
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:09,440
If news gets out about you and Ms. Fahsai

567
00:52:09,520 --> 00:52:12,560
having lunch together,
Mr. Rakchart won't be pleased.

568
00:52:15,680 --> 00:52:17,280
Why does everything
have to be divided into sides?

569
00:52:18,240 --> 00:52:19,520
What we're doing

570
00:52:19,600 --> 00:52:22,800
is for the people and the country.

571
00:52:24,680 --> 00:52:27,480
Save your charming words for campaigning.

572
00:52:31,240 --> 00:52:32,840
I'm just doing my job.

573
00:52:37,920 --> 00:52:41,400
I agree with Mr. Tarn
about not dividing sides.

574
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:47,360
This was just lunch between people

575
00:52:47,440 --> 00:52:49,320
helping the foundation.

576
00:52:52,680 --> 00:52:53,720
But…

577
00:53:00,400 --> 00:53:01,800
I agree with you.

578
00:53:04,520 --> 00:53:06,280
But I'll head back on my own.

579
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:14,560
I already took your whole day.
Thank you, and excuse me.

580
00:53:17,320 --> 00:53:18,320
Yes.

581
00:53:28,200 --> 00:53:29,400
Excuse me.

582
00:53:39,120 --> 00:53:41,880
If you agree with him,
why didn't you let him drive you?

583
00:53:42,520 --> 00:53:45,440
- I didn't want Dad or Samut to blame you.
- Huh?

584
00:53:48,680 --> 00:53:51,880
You're helping me.
I won't cause you trouble.

585
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:55,720
I'll go back with you,
but I have one request.

586
00:53:58,600 --> 00:54:02,120
Can you stop getting on my nerves?

587
00:54:03,760 --> 00:54:04,920
I beg you.

588
00:54:07,600 --> 00:54:08,440
Please.

589
00:54:25,120 --> 00:54:29,160
One more thing. I'm not going back to
the foundation yet. I'm going somewhere.

590
00:54:42,120 --> 00:54:44,520
While waiting earlier, I saw you
only drinking coffee.

591
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:45,880
This is on me.

592
00:54:48,480 --> 00:54:50,960
Why this place though?

593
00:54:52,480 --> 00:54:54,640
I thought you didn't like Chinese food.

594
00:54:57,720 --> 00:55:00,280
I saw in movies

595
00:55:00,360 --> 00:55:02,240
that mafia people
like to eat at Chinese restaurants.

596
00:55:06,760 --> 00:55:07,960
You saw that in a movie?

597
00:55:09,920 --> 00:55:11,160
Mafia 101?

598
00:55:12,800 --> 00:55:13,920
From a movie?

599
00:55:14,920 --> 00:55:17,240
If you don't like it, we can change.

600
00:55:18,840 --> 00:55:21,920
If it were a mafia like me,
I wouldn't eat at normal places.

601
00:55:24,320 --> 00:55:25,920
Someone like me

602
00:55:26,000 --> 00:55:29,400
would choose somewhere
you probably couldn't handle.

603
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:33,480
Then we'll just eat here.

604
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:36,120
Finish it and go to the place you want.

605
00:55:38,080 --> 00:55:39,640
But go alone.

606
00:55:46,240 --> 00:55:47,400
Excuse me.

607
00:55:48,240 --> 00:55:49,200
Thank you.

608
00:55:57,840 --> 00:55:59,160
The host eats first.

609
00:55:59,800 --> 00:56:02,880
I'm already full. You eat.
No need to serve me.

610
00:56:04,840 --> 00:56:09,000
Mafia 102, the host eats first.

611
00:56:22,240 --> 00:56:23,520
Can you eat now?

612
00:56:54,360 --> 00:56:55,960
The DNA results, sir.

613
00:56:57,400 --> 00:56:58,400
Thank you.

614
00:57:40,120 --> 00:57:41,800
Wayu isn't Black Doc.

615
00:57:43,160 --> 00:57:44,720
Then who the hell is Black Doc?

616
00:58:07,880 --> 00:58:11,360
By now, if they've got the DNA results,
their faces must've dropped.

617
00:58:37,680 --> 00:58:39,280
They fell right into our trap.

618
00:58:40,120 --> 00:58:42,320
They won't suspect me
as Black Doc anymore.

619
00:58:44,480 --> 00:58:47,600
See? If you had really
kept me out of this,

620
00:58:47,680 --> 00:58:50,520
you'd have been exposed by now.

621
00:58:52,800 --> 00:58:54,360
You were shot at the scene.

622
00:58:55,280 --> 00:58:57,360
The police
might've gotten Black Doc's blood.

623
00:58:58,200 --> 00:59:00,360
They'll definitely test the DNA.

624
00:59:01,960 --> 00:59:04,120
For now, you have to be extremely careful.

625
00:59:04,720 --> 00:59:08,080
Don't let anyone get anything from you,
not even a fingernail.

626
00:59:16,680 --> 00:59:19,640
MONTHLY CASE

627
00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:21,720
What is it?

628
00:59:28,240 --> 00:59:30,320
You have a nice office.

629
00:59:30,920 --> 00:59:31,960
Thank you.

630
00:59:46,840 --> 00:59:47,680
Thank you so much.

631
00:59:50,640 --> 00:59:53,920
But I really don't think
you should get involved in this.

632
00:59:56,280 --> 00:59:58,960
How many times
can you keep slipping past the police?

633
01:00:01,760 --> 01:00:02,680
Please stop.

634
01:00:04,080 --> 01:00:04,920
Okay?

635
01:00:25,600 --> 01:00:26,560
MS. PEEKUL

636
01:00:29,200 --> 01:00:32,760
What is Peekul Jaiaree to you, Captain?

637
01:00:34,960 --> 01:00:38,120
Someone like you, who only loves herself,

638
01:00:39,680 --> 01:00:42,200
doesn't know how to love
or care about anyone else.

639
01:00:47,800 --> 01:00:49,360
My boss asked me to give this to you.

640
01:00:50,600 --> 01:00:51,840
Uh, you…

641
01:01:02,560 --> 01:01:03,920
You got me beaten up!

642
01:02:01,560 --> 01:02:04,600
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
